{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2030"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of man-made fibres"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2030"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :man-made-fibre/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :materials-safety :resource-efficiency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :man-made-fibre-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae :cfd]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "FibreAdvisor ⊣ Man-Made Fibre Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for man-made-fibre manufacturing (spinning/extrusion/drawing
 lines producing continuous filament or staple fibre from synthetic
 polymers such as polyester/nylon/acrylic or regenerated cellulose such
 as viscose rayon) -- not direct spinning/extrusion-line-equipment
 control authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Ten concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct spinning/extrusion-line-equipment control),
 permanent line-actuate block, independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-weight recompute against the batch's own logged
 weight, double-schedule guard, fibre-type validation, and denier
 plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging (chemical-hazard
 solvent-exposure/equipment-safety) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant
 supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
